Kīrtisiṃha, the illegitimate son of King Siddhinarasiṃha Malla, built a three-storied temple at Swãtha on the 4th of Vaiśākha, NS 789 (Bhāṣāvaṃśāvalī 1966: 69). It is said that Kirtisiṃha built this for his first wife. The story goes that, some time later (ca.NS 781), he constructed a stone temple next to the previous one to appease his jealous second wife. Kirtisiṃha supposedly built three Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa temples in total.
